<br>
Bleh.<br>
<br>
If you're sitting at the zone line, like with the zone to Kith which is a sort of pass/valley thing, then you ought to be prepared to zone if a train comes through. That's just part of the price of choosing to sit at the zone line rather than a little bit to the side of the zone line.<br>
<br>
I always TRY to announce trains, but if I'm just barely keeping ahead of it by using mouselook/strafe, sometimes I don't have a chance to switch hotkey banks and hit my train button. Much less type out anything close to coherent. I need more fingers. And if I see you sitting nearby, I'll try to detour around you. But if you're sitting on the train tracks, and it was one of those cases where I just couldn't call it out ahead of time... well, that falls into the &quot;hey, it's EQ, it happens&quot; category. The zone IS right there. Even if an unannounced train suddenly starts hitting you, if you're sitting right at the zone you can <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> usually</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> escape anyway.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey, it's EQ, it happens,&quot; is usually my reaction when someone apologizes to me for a train, too. Just not worth getting worked up over, unless the guy obviously did it on purpose.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhalus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Halus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/28/02 4:49:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=419.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Die like a real elf!</span><hr size=1> Especially on this server, where shout is fairly useless, it's pretty pointless to get mad about a train at the zone. <br>
