N>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 577<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/28/02 8:57:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=419.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_bigsmile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Zone!</span><hr size=1> If they're at the zone or otherwise on the tracks, they really should be ready and able to move.  I recall one time I had a train and the group just stood there and watched until I FD'd (at 12 hp).  The train then proceeded to pound them and one died.  I was equally upset at them for watching when they should have been running and myself for causing a death -- even a death that I felt they could have avoided.<br>
<br>
